data.description: All I have to say is Welcome Home! This house has timeless hardwood floors all throughout. Love hosting? The beautiful dining room features two sets of French doors which open to a deck overlooking the neighboring lake. The kitchen is a dream for those who love to cook. Butcher block countertops, farmhouse sink, soft close cabinet/drawers, double oven, and SO MUCH STORAGE! The corner cabinet even has a pull out organizer. Just imagine grabbing a cup of joe and enjoying a peaceful morning from the deck. Talk about serenity!   The master bed/bath is located on one side of the house while two smaller bedrooms are on the other, separated by the spacious living room. The marble in the bathrooms is absolutely gorgeous. Think about the memories you will make with your kids playing in the yard, on the large playset, and in the treehouse!   Did I mention the second level? At the top of the stairs you will find a bonus room that is perfect for a game room, craft room, homeschool classroom, or home office! The possibilities are endless. On your left is the 4th bedroom.  Across from the stairs is the mudroom/laundry room. If I’m honest, this is my favorite room. This room has so much to offer. Space for your washer and dryer, space to hang clothes, store boots, work jackets, tools, etc. You can enter from the front driveway and exit onto the back deck without having to go through the rest of the house with dirty shoes.   The Tallapoosa River VPA surrounds the property as well. For those with hunters in your family, that’s public hunting land!  To find out what else this lovely property has to offer, give us a call!   **Lake mentioned above and in photos is not being sold as part of listed property.**
